title: For Sale:  Ruger M77
postcontent: Got elk?  Got bear?  Got grizz........!?  Old Ruger M77 rifle in the 338 Winchester Magnum cartridge.  Came out of an estate, and had been sitting muzzle down in a closet for the past 25 years +/-.. The serial number puts the manufacture at 1974.  The barrel in the carpet was pretty rusted, in and out, so I cut the worst off of it - gunsmith said about 2" - and had a brake added. The original 24" barrel is now about the same, but with a brake.  The slight pitting on the barrel and receiver came out, then I Duracoated everything in HK Black.  The bore looks very nice after a good scrubbing, and probably wasn't fired more than a box of shells in it's life.  I refinished the wood stock as well while adding a Decelerator recoil pad, but didn't spend alot of time on it.  The Leupold 4x needed coating as well, but it's still a fine old optic.  I did not and will not re-zero the scope.  That will be entirely up to the proud new owner.  This dangerous game caliber isn't something you want to take out every weeekend and shoot.  The rifle maybe weighs 8 pounds soaking wet, so the recoil is pretty harsh, but it may be a little tamer with the recoil pad and brake.  Not interested in trades, and I'll cover the FFL at Magnum Shooting Center in Colorado Springs.  Any other location will be on the buyer.

No Greater Sacrifice is committed to providing a debt-free college education to the children of our nation’s fallen and severely wounded Service Members. Since 2008, No Greater Sacrifice has awarded 133 scholarships to the children of these American Heroes, committing over $8 million towards their higher educational pursuits. In addition to providing a debt-free education to these children, No Greater Sacrifice also offers personalized mentorship to each scholarship recipient, to help them excel in their higher educational endeavors. By focusing on the children of our fallen and severely wounded Service Members, No Greater Sacrifice recognizes and honors the sacrifices of the entire family in defense of freedom, and lifts a huge financial burden from these families who have given so much to our nation.
